I do the same sort of thing Jordan does, when I need to redirect mail
delivery I only have to remove one .forward file in the path (or redirect
one .forward file, etc).

There are two issues here that need to be addressed. First is that
not every host on the Internet has the capability to forward mail,
so putting that capacity *somewhere* is very important. The domain
system is one of many places to put it.

Second, is that you don't have to use the mechanism if you don't want
to. Administrative types aren't forcing domain mailboxing down your
throat (and if they do it is a local issue, rather than a network-wide
edict).

cheers,
--jsol

